    title: "FULLSTACK HYBRIS \u0026 REACT DEVELOPER",
    description:
      '\u003cp\u003eG-Star is a place where your passion for all things jeans becomes a career. It’s a place of collaboration, inspiration, and innovation. Working alongside like-minded people, feeding off one another’s energy and drive. It’s a place to express and grow your specialization, in a dynamic environment that values proactivity and innovation. A ‘Dutch’ approach to communication encourages openness and clarity within our relatively flat organization. It’s a place where the level of responsibility is equal to the level of fun. Hands on to get things done, we strive to make the impossible possible. At G-Star, every day is another opportunity to push the boundaries of denim.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJob description\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHere’s what we’ll do together:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eG-Star is looking for an Experienced Fullstack Hybris \u0026amp; React developer to join the eCommerce IT-team. The eCommerce IT-team (+-30 FTE) is based in our global headquarter in Amsterdam and consists of a couple of Scrum teams working on technical support and new functionalities for the online presence of G-Star at \u003ca href="http://www.g-star.com"\u003ewww.g-star.com\u003c/a\u003e. In this role you will be involved in many aspects of the software development lifecycle: from gathering \u0026amp; refining technical requirements to implementing new features and functionality backed by unit tests.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eJust Imagine – as our Fullstack Hybris \u0026amp; React Developer, you will be part of a team of internal \u0026amp; external Java and ReactJS developers applying best practices developing within the Hybris platform. Together with other members of the team, you will be responsible for specifying technical solutions for new business requirements and implementations while maintaining an overview of how the Hybris system integrates with the rest of the IT landscape.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTasks \u0026amp; responsibilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDefine technical solutions for business requirements\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWrite code to satisfy the business requirements and technical specifications (applying your experience and best practices in Hybris and React development)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDocument changes in the knowledgebase \u0026amp; within the code\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWrite manuals for business users if creating new functionality within the system\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMaintain a good level of test coverage as defined by the team\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat you bring to the table:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have experience working in E-Commerce for retail\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProgramming Java/J2EE and ReactJS? Nothing you haven’t done before.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou bring experience in working in intense, technical team environments. You also have experience in working in an Agile/Scrum environment.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have a strong interest in the the creative process and the various production processes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have high learning capabilities.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have knowledge of JIRA, Confluence, BitBucket/GIT and a pro-active, practical and hands-on approach.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAdd a Bachelor or Masters degree in a relevant field of studies and a minimum of 2 years (hands-on) experience with both Hybris and ReactJS, and you’ve got our full attention.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAre you also an excellent communicator? We’re heart-eyed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFinally, are you fluent in English? We’d love to meet you!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProfile\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat we bring to the table:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBeyond a competitive salary, working at G-Star brings many other perks and exciting opportunities: an awesome and diverse team that collaborates to change the game; a work environment that offers room for fun, inspiration and innovation; a clothing budget and a healthy, fresh and delicious lunch;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat will happen next:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWe will thoroughly review your CV.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWe have a large expat community at G-Star, so please apply in English via the application form.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWhen we hopefully find what we are looking for, we will call you for a chat and if it’s a good fit, we’ll plan our first interview.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBecause we’re very curious how you’d survive a mission impossible, we ask you to prepare a real-life business case in a follow-up interview.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWhen we’re ready to commit to each other, we’ll finalize the terms we’ve discussed and we’ll explain to you how to order your first pair of jeans from the G-Star employee store. Good luck.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href="https://g-starraw.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/fullstack_hybris_react_developer_amsterdam/257775/V819/solliciteren"\u003eClick here to apply!\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n',
